               <code code="34088-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="OVERDOSAGE SECTION"/>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="bold">OVERDOSAGE:</content> Topically applied corticosteroids can be absorbed in sufficient amounts to produce systemic effects. (See 
       
 
  
       
 
  <linkHtml href="#AS300">PRECAUTIONS.</linkHtml>)
       
 
  
       
 
  <br/>
                  </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20150805"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
            <section ID="AS100">
               <id root="6061fb5a-a9f5-1630-e053-2991aa0ac4d8"/>
               <code code="34068-7" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DOSAGE &amp; ADMINISTRATION SECTION"/>
               <text>
                  <paragraph/>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="bold">DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION:</content> Topical corticosteroids are generally applied to the
affected area as a thin film three to four times daily depending on the
severity of the condition. Occlusive dressings may be used for the management
of psoriasis or recalcitrant conditions. If an infection develops, the use of
occlusive dressings should be discontinued and appropriate antimicrobial
therapy instituted.
      

 
      

 </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20150805"/>
            </section>
